[normal]3.8.
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]Access to medical services is a fundamental need of all residents, and each of the 6 segments identified in Table 6 require access to some level of medical provision. This is the largest of the six individual service 
[normal]networks demonstrating that almost 30,000 households are heavily reliant on public transport to access medical services in the East Riding. Figure 20 shows where the main routes would be required in the network to provide an adequate network for serving me
[normal]dical establishments:
